      ],
      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "quotient of the number of specified data elements transferred in a time interval by the duration of this interval",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "The symbol stem:[nu] is the Greek letter nu.\n\nA subscript referring to a specified data element can\nbe added to the symbol.\n\n[example]\ndigit rate, stem:[r_d] or stem:[nu_d] (see <<iec60050-702,droploc%locality:item=\"702-05-23\">> and\n<<iec60050-704,droploc%locality:item=\"704-16-06\">>); +\ntransfer rate for octets (or bytes), stem:[r_o, r_B, nu_o] or stem:[nu_B];\nbinary digit rate or bit rate (<<t13-13,item 13-13>>).\n\nIn English, the name \"byte\", symbol B, is used as a\nsynonym for \"octet\". Here \"byte\" means an eight-bit\nbyte. See remarks in <<t13-9,item 13-9>>.\n\nThe octet per second (or byte per second) may be\ncombined with prefixes, for example kilooctet per\nsecond, symbol ko/s (or kilobyte per second, symbol\nkB/s).\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "isoiec80000:hasUnit": [
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-s^{-1}"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-o/s"
        },
        {
          "@id": "isoiec80000:unit-B/s"
        }
      ],
